From: =?UTF-8?q?Toke=20H=C3=B8iland-J=C3=B8rgensen?= <toke@redhat.com>
Date: Mon, 12 Aug 2024 16:24:46 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath9k_htc: Use __skb_set_length() for resetting urb
 before resubmit
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 94745807f3ebd379f23865e6dab196f220664179
Patch-mainline: v6.12-rc1
References: CVE-2024-49938 bsc#1232552

Syzbot points out that skb_trim() has a sanity check on the existing length of
the skb, which can be uninitialised in some error paths. The intent here is
clearly just to reset the length to zero before resubmitting, so switch to
calling __skb_set_length(skb, 0) directly. In addition, __skb_set_length()
already contains a call to skb_reset_tail_pointer(), so remove the redundant
call.

The syzbot report came from ath9k_hif_usb_reg_in_cb(), but there's a similar
usage of skb_trim() in ath9k_hif_usb_rx_cb(), change both while we're at it.

Reported-by: syzbot+98afa303be379af6cdb2@syzkaller.appspotmail.com
Signed-off-by: Toke Høiland-Jørgensen <toke@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Kalle Valo <quic_kvalo@quicinc.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20240812142447.12328-1-toke@toke.dk
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath9k/hif_usb.c |    6 ++----
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath9k/hif_usb.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath9k/hif_usb.c
@@ -681,8 +681,7 @@ static void ath9k_hif_usb_rx_cb(struct u
 	}
 
 resubmit:
-	skb_reset_tail_pointer(skb);
-	skb_trim(skb, 0);
+	__skb_set_length(skb, 0);
 
 	usb_anchor_urb(urb, &hif_dev->rx_submitted);
 	ret = usb_submit_urb(urb, GFP_ATOMIC);
@@ -719,8 +718,7 @@ static void ath9k_hif_usb_reg_in_cb(stru
 	case -ESHUTDOWN:
 		goto free;
 	default:
-		skb_reset_tail_pointer(skb);
-		skb_trim(skb, 0);
+		__skb_set_length(skb, 0);
 
 		goto resubmit;
 	}
